I have a few questions:<br>
<br>
Is there really an effective way for a wizard to solo for experience? How?<br>
<br>
What is quad kiting? <br>
<br>
At level 35 what spells should I have memed when soloing?<br>
<br>
Where are some good places to solo my wizard at 35 for <br>
a) Experience <br>
and <br>
b) some good sellable items.<br>
<br>
 <p>------
Endurance</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uheihache.showPublicProfile?language=EN>heihache</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/6/01 10:52:18 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.iquest.net/~jynx25/me.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I have never soloed my wizard</span><hr size=1> Is there really an effective way for a wizard to solo for experience? How?<br>
Yep, pre 29 root and nuke is about the only way to solo.  Post 29 snare kite (ala druid).  <br>
<br>
What is quad kiting? <br>
Quad Kiting is the art of kiting 4 mobs at the same time, and in theory, having them all die at the same time for some very nice XP.  A friendly wizard named Grimstaff wrote a very nice article.  Link is below:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.angelfire.com/or2/Wizards/quad.html">www.angelfire.com/or2/Wizards/quad.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
At level 35 what spells should I have memed when soloing?<br>
That depends on where your hunting.  Here are the spells I always had mem'd regardless:<br>
Harvest, gate, Bonds of Force, immobilize.<br>
<br>
Where are some good places to solo my wizard at 35 for <br>
a) Experience <br>
and <br>
b) some good sellable items.<br>
For xp, check out snow cougars in Iceclad.  Very good xp and they rarely drop the cougar claw earing.  Once you get 38, kill the snow dervs near the portal in Iceclad.  Or, there is always the overthere.  For loot, solo the AC in upper guk, or get a group in L guk and camp items. <p><a href=#><img src=http://members.iquest.net/~jynx25/robe.jpg border=0></a>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umelonwy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Melonwy</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.themelee.com/smilies/s/otn/angels/bat_angel.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/6/01 10:27:43 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.themelee.com/smilies/s/kao/otn/pangel1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I have never soloed my wizard</span><hr size=1> I have rarely soloed my wizard.  But at this point, my thinking is I should do it more.  There is a post in this forum about soloing the drolvargs in Firiona.  I have actually tried that and it worked.  Lots of NPC's roaming around to help you out if you need it.  Most con blue to me at 35.  Watch out for the Firiona Drakes and the Pilgrims.  If you get to close, they will kill steal.  But it isn't really their fault.  <br>
<br>
Down time is inevitable.  You gotta med sometime.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Always have root and bonds of force mem'd.  If one doesn't hold, the other should.  Always have your two highest DD's and a lower one for when mana gets low.  Of course, always have gate just in case something MAJOR goes wrong.  Harvest is great.  Never go anywhere without it.  <br>
<br>
I feel like I am repeating a bit of Heihache's post.  But if you want more information on soloing.  There are some fine posts on how and where to do so.  Ya' just have to sort of look for them. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src="http://members.home.net/archer628/rof/mel.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uempoxnor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Empoxnor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/9/01 9:04:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I have never soloed my wizard</span><hr size=1> Well you should try to keep grouping it will be a skill that you don't want to let rust. Unless you quad kite I can't imagine that you will find better xp. It might be comparable xp but thats all. It also depends if you get good groups or your groups always fall apart. Also if you group chances are you will get some good items in your journies. <br>
<br>
At high levels grouping is the way to go for the most part. The few solo spots that are good normally are so contested or camped its not worth the time it takes to get the spawn. So keep grouping <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
